factors for engineering work\"}],[\"$\",\"p\",null,{\"className\":\"mt-1 text-sm text-muted-foreground\",\"children\":\"Every conversion factor in the tool comes from NIST reference data or published engineering tables. For lab reports or design calculations, this matters — internet-scraped factors often round at the third decimal and accumulate error across multi-step conversions.\"}]]}]]}],[\"$\",\"li\",\"Switch precision based on context\",{\"className\":\"flex gap-3 rounded-lg border border-border bg-card p-4\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"$Lf\",null,{\"iconNode\":\"$b:props:children:2:0:props:children:2:props:children:0:props:children:0:props:iconNode\",\"className\":\"lucide-lightbulb mt-0.5 size-5 shrink-0 text-brand\"}],[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"children\":[[\"$\",\"h3\",null,{\"className\":\"text-sm font-semibold\",\"children\":\"Switch precision based on context\"}],[\"$\",\"p\",null,{\"className\":\"mt-1 text-sm text-muted-foreground\",\"children\":\"The tool defaults to 6 significant digits but supports up to 15. Use 4–6 for everyday work; use 12–15 only when you're carrying error through a long calculation chain.\"}]]}]]}],[\"$\",\"li\",\"Batch convert when comparing a range\",{\"className\":\"flex gap-3 rounded-lg border border-border bg-card p-4\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"$Lf\",null,{\"iconNode\":\"$b:props:children:2:0:props:children:2:props:children:0:props:children:0:props:iconNode\",\"className\":\"lucide-lightbulb mt-0.5 size-5 shrink-0 text-brand\"}],[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"children\":[[\"$\",\"h3\",null,{\"className\":\"text-sm font-semibold\",\"children\":\"Batch convert when comparing a range\"}],[\"$\",\"p\",null,{\"className\":\"mt-1 text-sm text-muted-foreground\",\"children\":\"When you need the same conversion across many values (10, 20, 50, 100 psi → bar), batch mode runs them all at once instead of you retyping the source value.\"}]]}]]}],[\"$\",\"li\",\"Read the formula bar — it shows the relationship\",{\"className\":\"flex gap-3 rounded-lg border border-border bg-card p-4\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"$Lf\",null,{\"iconNode\":\"$b:props:children:2:0:props:children:2:props:children:0:props:children:0:props:iconNode\",\"className\":\"lucide-lightbulb mt-0.5 size-5 shrink-0 text-brand\"}],[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"children\":[[\"$\",\"h3\",null,{\"className\":\"text-sm font-semibold\",\"children\":\"Read the formula bar — it shows the relationship\"}],[\"$\",\"p\",null,{\"className\":\"mt-1 text-sm text-muted-foreground\",\"children\":\"The formula display isn't decoration. It shows the actual math (e.g., bar = psi × 0.0689476) so you can verify the conversion is what you expect, or use it in a spreadsheet later.\"}]]}]]}]]}]]}],\"$L13\",\"$L14\"]]}]\nc:[\"$\",\"script\",\"script-0\",{\"src\":\"/_next/static/chunks/0xbglb6k6reej.js\",\"async\":true}]\nd:[\"$\",\"$L15\",null,{\"children\":[\"$\",\"$16\",null,{\"name\":\"Next.MetadataOutlet\",\"children\":\"$@17\"}]}]\n13:[\"$\",\"section\",null,{\"aria-labelledby\":\"tool-insights-mistakes\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"h2\",null,{\"id\":\"tool-insights-mistakes\",\"className\":\"text-2xl font-semibold tracking-tight\",\"children\":\"Common Mistakes to Avoid\"}],[\"$\",\"ul\",null,{\"className\":\"mt-4 grid max-w-3xl gap-3\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"li\",\"Mixing absolute and gauge pressure\",{\"className\":\"flex gap-3 rounded-lg border border-border bg-card p-4\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"$Lf\",null,{\"iconNode\":[[\"path\",{\"d\":\"m21.73 18-8-14a2 2 0 0 0-3.48 0l-8 14A2 2 0 0 0 4 21h16a2 2 0 0 0 1.73-3\",\"key\":\"wmoenq\"}],[\"path\",{\"d\":\"M12 9v4\",\"key\":\"juzpu7\"}],[\"path\",{\"d\":\"M12 17h.01\",\"key\":\"p32p05\"}]],\"className\":\"lucide-triangle-alert mt-0.5 size-5 shrink-0 text-pink-500\"}],[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"children\":[[\"$\",\"h3\",null,{\"className\":\"text-sm font-semibold\",\"children\":\"Mixing absolute and gauge pressure\"}],[\"$\",\"p\",null,{\"className\":\"mt-1 text-sm text-muted-foreground\",\"children\":\"psi and psia/psig are not interchangeable. Gauge pressure is relative to atmospheric (~14.7 psi). A conversion from \\\"psi\\\" to \\\"bar\\\" gives different answers depending on which the source meant — verify before converting.\"}]]}]]}],[\"$\",\"li\",\"Confusing kg with kgf\",{\"className\":\"flex gap-3 rounded-lg border border-border bg-card p-4\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"$Lf\",null,{\"iconNode\":\"$13:props:children:1:props:children:0:props:children:0:props:iconNode\",\"className\":\"lucide-triangle-alert mt-0.5 size-5 shrink-0 text-pink-500\"}],[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"children\":[[\"$\",\"h3\",null,{\"className\":\"text-sm font-semibold\",\"children\":\"Confusing kg with kgf\"}],[\"$\",\"p\",null,{\"className\":\"mt-1 text-sm text-muted-foreground\",\"children\":\"Kilogram is mass; kilogram-force is a weight (mass × g). Engineering calcs often mix them up, producing answers off by ~9.81×. Pick mass units for mass and force units for force.\"}]]}]]}],[\"$\",\"li\",\"Using the wrong temperature scale offset\",{\"className\":\"flex gap-3 rounded-lg border border-border bg-card p-4\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"$Lf\",null,{\"iconNode\":\"$13:props:children:1:props:children:0:props:children:0:props:iconNode\",\"className\":\"lucide-triangle-alert mt-0.5 size-5 shrink-0 text-pink-500\"}],[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"children\":[[\"$\",\"h3\",null,{\"className\":\"text-sm font-semibold\",\"children\":\"Using the wrong temperature scale offset\"}],[\"$\",\"p\",null,{\"className\":\"mt-1 text-sm text-muted-foreground\",\"children\":\"Celsius/Fahrenheit conversions are offsets, not ratios. 0°C ≠ 0°F. The tool handles this correctly — but if you're scripting your own conversion, the offset trips most people up.\"}]]}]]}],[\"$\",\"li\",\"Ignoring significant figures from the source\",{\"className\":\"flex gap-3 rounded-lg border border-border bg-card p-4\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"$Lf\",null,{\"iconNode\":\"$13:props:children:1:props:children:0:props:children:0:props:iconNode\",\"className\":\"lucide-triangle-alert mt-0.5 s